                              FluidSynth-DSSI
                              ===============
                    A software synthesizer plugin  for the
                        Disposable Soft Synth Interface

NOTE
====
This is an ALPHA snapshot.  Please do not redistribute.

Introduction
============
This package is a !FIX! implementation of a FluidSynth DSSI plugin,
capable of sharing in-memory soundfont data between multiple plugin
instances.

Requirements
============
You need to have the following installed:

   liblo 0.5 or 0.6
   fluidsynth 1.0.3 (including libfluidsynth)
   DSSI, ALSA, LADSPA, and JACK

You must also have the fluidsynth 1.0.3 source code unpacked
somewhere accessible.

Installation
============
Edit the Makefile, then do 'make'.  There is no 'make install' yet.

Operation
=========
!FIX! There's a GUI now!

!FIX! available 'configure' messages:

   dssi_osc_send -C <osc-url> load /usr/share/sf2/soundfont.sf2

   dssi_osc_send -C <osc-url> gain 0.5

!FIX! note that gain is global to all the fs instances, so you better
send the same gain to each instance or thing may not be repeatable...

Each instance may use only one soundfont at a time, but when
multiple instances use the same soundfont, it is only loaded once.

Example
=======
1. Start JACK.

2. Run the dssi_example_host, starting 16 FluidSynth-DSSI instances,
    one for each MIDI channel:

    $ DSSI_PATH=/home/smbolton/src/fluidsynth-dssi-0.1.0 sudo ./dssi_example_host -16 fluidsynth-dssi.so

3. Load a soundfont for each instance:

    $ for ee in 00 01 02 03 04 05 06 07 08 09 10 11 12 13 14 15
    > do dssi_osc_send -C osc.udp://localhost:19383/dssi/fluidsynth-dssi/FluidSynth-DSSI/chan$ee \
    >      load /t/soundfonts/Reality_GMGS.sf2
    > done

4. Make some noise:

    $ pmidi -p128:0 /t/smf/simpsons_theme.mid

